ast_Centre\"}, {\"begin\": 331, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gangneung\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7699627310839416e-14, \"text\": \"Gangneung\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gangneung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gangneung\"}, {\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999892538655, \"rank\": 5.908401261130344e-09, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Gangwon 2024 Winter Youth Olympic Games\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP The hosts of the next Winter Youth Olympic Games (YOG) will not be announced on Thursday as Gangwon 2024 in South Korea draws close, but it will be revealed no later than early 2025, according to International Olympic Committee President (IOC) Thomas Bach earlier today.\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 429, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.376094988511463e-15, \"text\": \"YOG\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 487, \"end\": 498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999892538655, \"rank\": 5.908401261130344e-09, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olym